The paper focuses on learning touch gestures on big touch devices, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The proposed method uses deep neural networks, specifically convolutional models, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a new touch gestures dataset, which could potentially fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) categories.
